  "prompt": "How do I get person online status when he is on whatsapp call?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, WhatsApp does not provide a direct way for users to check the online status of a contact when they are on a call. Privacy is a significant concern for WhatsApp, and the app is designed to protect the user's online status and activity from being tracked by others.\n\nWhen someone is on a call, their online status may change to \"busy\" or might simply not be displayed as \"online\". However, how their status is presented can vary based on their settings and whether you are in their contacts.\n\nIf you want to know if someone is on a call, the best approach is to communicate with them directly or wait until they are available. Always prioritize respecting others\u2019 privacy and avoid using third-party applications or methods that may violate WhatsApp\u2019s terms of service.",
